GM recalls new Pickup Trucks in the USA for the repair of the backrest
General Motors recalls scarcely 19,000 of its brand-new Chevrolet Silverado and GMC Sierra Pickup Trucks with year of construction 2014, in order to repair a problem with the manually adjustable backrest, so a report of the US-American regulatory authority for vehicle safety on Friday.
With some the car can give it a defect in the mechanism for resetting to the front seat backrest.
For this reason they do not fulfill the federal guidelines for the vehicle safety with head restraints.
„If from the rear into the vehicle, is possible it is driven that the head restraint does not protect the passengers correctly, so that a increased injury risk exists” to read was in the message on the website of the national highway Traffic Safety administration (NHTSA).
The recalled models were manufactured between 1 August and 10 September.
The delivery of the GM-Trucks began in June and represents the most important model start of the prominent US-American automaker since the insolvency-conditioned restructuring 2009.
GM informed the owners of vehicle in the first October half about the defect.
The NHTSA could not check the letter of advice because of the 16-day Government shutdown, what affected the car sales negatively in October.
The sale of the Silverado and Sierra Trucks, which were again developed for model year 2014, rose in the first ten months of the year by 20 percent, explained GM on Friday.
In October GM sold 42,660 Silverado and 16,503 Sierra Pickup Trucks.
The GM share rose at the New York Stock Exchange by 1,4 percent to 37,47 US Dollar on Friday afternoon.
